---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TwoColumnLayout from "../layouts/TwoColumnLayout.astro";
import Ornament from "../components/Ornament.astro";
import { visionariesCampaign } from "../data/site";

const description =
  "Chris Busse has been nominated for Blood Cancer United's Visionaries of the Year in Richmond. Learn why and how you can help fund the fight against blood cancer.";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Visionaries of the Year"
  description={description}
>
  <TwoColumnLayout>
    <article>
      <header class="visionaries-hero">
        <p class="visionaries-kicker">Blood Cancer United</p>
        <h1>Visionaries of the Year</h1>
        <p class="lead-text">
          I've been nominated as a Visionary of the Year candidate in Richmond.
          This is a ten-week fundraising campaign in honor of local blood cancer
          survivors — and every dollar raised goes directly to research, patient
          support, and advocacy that is changing what it means to hear the words
          "you have blood cancer."
        </p>
      </header>

      <h2>Why This Matters</h2>

      <p>
        Every five minutes, someone in the United States is diagnosed with a blood
        cancer.<sup><a href="#fn-1" id="ref-1">1</a></sup> Leukemia, lymphoma,
        myeloma, and myelodysplastic syndromes collectively represent the
        third-leading cause of cancer death in the U.S., ahead of breast cancer
        and prostate cancer.<sup><a href="#fn-2" id="ref-2">2</a></sup>
      </p>

      <p>
        Blood Cancer United — formerly The Leukemia &amp; Lymphoma Society — is
        the world's largest nonprofit funder of blood cancer research. Since 1949,
        they have invested more than $2 billion in groundbreaking research, and
        their work has been instrumental in advancing more than 70 percent of the
        blood cancer treatments approved by the FDA over the past two
        decades.<sup><a href="#fn-3" id="ref-3">3</a></sup>
      </p>

      <p>
        That is not a marketing number. It represents a transformation in survival
        rates that was unimaginable a generation ago. In 2022 alone, Blood Cancer
        United committed $233.8 million in multi-year research funding, supporting
        more than 220 scientists at leading institutions
        worldwide.<sup><a href="#fn-4" id="ref-4">4</a></sup>
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <p>
        Their Therapy Acceleration Program partners directly with biotech companies
        to fast-track promising treatments through clinical trials. Their Beat AML
        master trial is pioneering precision medicine for acute myeloid leukemia.
        Their funding helped develop CAR T-cell therapy — a treatment in which a
        patient's own immune cells are re-engineered to attack cancer — which led
        to the FDA approval of axicabtagene ciloleucel, the first CAR T-cell
        therapy for lymphoma.<sup><a href="#fn-5" id="ref-5">5</a></sup>
      </p>

      <p>
        More recently, over a decade of Blood Cancer United-funded research
        establishing CD38 as a treatment target led to the development of
        daratumumab, now a cornerstone of multiple myeloma treatment. The FDA
        approved a combination therapy built on that work as recently as March
        2026.<sup><a href="#fn-6" id="ref-6">6</a></sup>
      </p>

      <p>
        Beyond research, Blood Cancer United provides free educational resources
        and support programs for patients and families navigating diagnosis and
        treatment. They have mobilized more than 100,000 volunteer advocates
        across the country to fight for policies that protect patients' access to
        care.<sup><a href="#fn-7" id="ref-7">7</a></sup>
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>My Why</h2>

      <p>
        <!-- Replace this with your personal story and motivation -->
        <em>[Your personal connection to this cause goes here. Why does this
        matter to you? Who are you fighting for?]</em>
      </p>

      <div class="visionaries-goal">
        <p class="visionaries-kicker">Campaign Goal</p>
        <span class="goal-amount">{visionariesCampaign.goal}</span>
        <p>
          Every dollar goes to Blood Cancer United's mission: curing blood cancer
          and improving the quality of life of patients and their families.
        </p>
        <a href={visionariesCampaign.fundraisingUrl} class="visionaries-cta">
          Donate Now
        </a>
      </div>

      <Ornament />

      <section class="visionaries-footnotes" aria-label="References">
        <h2 id="references">References</h2>
        <ol>
          <li id="fn-1">
            Blood Cancer United, "Blood Cancer Facts and Statistics."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/blood-cancer/blood-cancer-facts-and-statistics">
              bloodcancerunited.org/blood-cancer/blood-cancer-facts-and-statistics
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-1" aria-label="Back to reference 1">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-2">
            Blood Cancer United, "Blood Cancer Facts and Statistics."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/blood-cancer/blood-cancer-facts-and-statistics">
              bloodcancerunited.org/blood-cancer/blood-cancer-facts-and-statistics
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-2" aria-label="Back to reference 2">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-3">
            Blood Cancer United, "Blood Cancer Research."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/research/blood-cancer-research-development-progress">
              bloodcancerunited.org/research/blood-cancer-research-development-progress
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-3" aria-label="Back to reference 3">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-4">
            Blood Cancer United, "Our Impact on Blood Cancer Research."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/research/blood-cancer-research-development-progress">
              bloodcancerunited.org/research/blood-cancer-research-development-progress
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-4" aria-label="Back to reference 4">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-5">
            Blood Cancer United, "LLS Research Spotlight."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/lls-research-spotlight">
              bloodcancerunited.org/lls-research-spotlight
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-5" aria-label="Back to reference 5">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-6">
            Blood Cancer United, "FDA Approves Combination Treatment for Multiple Myeloma."
            <a href="https://bloodcancerunited.org/resources/newsroom/fda-approves-combination-treatment-multiple-myeloma">
              bloodcancerunited.org/resources/newsroom/fda-approves-combination-treatment-multiple-myeloma
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-6" aria-label="Back to reference 6">↩</a>
          </li>
          <li id="fn-7">
            Blood Cancer United, "Visionaries of the Year."
            <a href="https://www.llsvisionaries.org/">
              llsvisionaries.org
            </a>
            <a href="#ref-7" aria-label="Back to reference 7">↩</a>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>
    </article>
  </TwoColumnLayout>
</BaseLayout>
